data.title: Carmen Electra, 41, flashes toned midriff in white crop-top and stone-wash jeans at Hollywood club
data.meta_description: She's in the midst of reviving her singing career
data.text:
She's in the midst of reviving her singing career.

And Carmen Electra proved she could still rule a night club after 40 while attending the Krewella album release party at Exchange LA Monday.

SCROLL DOWN FOR VIDEO

Faux Skrillex hair: The former Prince muse - born Tara Patrick - rocked cat-eye make-up and put the left side of her hair into cornrows

The former Pussycat Doll and British singer Mams Taylor released a cheeky new EDM-inspired song called Bigger D**k last May.

The Baywatch beauty looked far more elegant in a nude sequined gown at the annual Voices on Point dinner and concert earlier this month.

Carmen was last romantically linked to Olympic swimmer Ryan Lochte, whom she was spotted kissing at a Hollywood hot spot in March.

Frontwoman: Carmen's last concert was at The Factory's Club Papi in San Francisco on September 14

'My babes': Carmen posted this Instagram of her dancers Erin Yvonne and Samantha Abrantes rocking rave-style braided extensions

Rehearsal: The former Pussycat Doll and British singer Mams Taylor released a cheeky new EDM-inspired song called Bigger D**k last May

Electra's renewed interest in her music career might have something to do with having dated Simon Cowell earlier this year.

The Disaster Movie actress previously romanced musicians Tommy Lee, Fred Durst, Rob Patterson, Prince, and her ex-husband is Dave Navarro.

She has three films coming out in November - action flick Book of Fire, the musical Dragula, and the comedy Oy Vey! My Son is Gay!!
